This paper is about improving the accuracy of pixel labeling tasks such as semantic segmentation, object localization, and image categorization using dense prediction models. These tasks are all related to computer vision, which suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes new layers (eConv and ePool) that are equivalent to the baseline CNN model, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the transferability of parameters between the dense model and the original model, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions age estimation, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
